The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 Mumbai, Aug. 29: State-run Oil India Limited (OIL) is likely to form a joint venture with a US-based company to acquire shale gas assets globally, a top official said. We are negotiating with a couple of US-based shale gas companies to form a JV. This will enable us in terms of technology in shale gas exploration and also help us in acquiring shale gas assets globally, OIL chairman and managing director N.M. Borah said.                             
	 London, Aug. 29: Vodafone is to sell its shares in China Mobile to raise more than 4 billion ($6.2 billion), The Sunday Times has reported. The deal with China Telecom is expected to be the first in a series of planned sell-offs Vodafone will make in the coming months.                             
	 Mumbai, Aug. 29: The Container Corporation of India (Concor) is likely to ink a joint venture with global shipping majors to cater to exim trade requirements. Concor is in talks to form a JV to provide international freight logistics services, Concors chief general manager (western region) P.K. Agrawal said.                            
	 Mumbai, Aug. 29: Gold prices are set to touch Rs 19,500-20,000 per 10 grams by Diwali because of rising investor interest. We expect gold prices to cross Rs 19,500-Rs 20,000 per 10 grams by Diwali this year after some correction in prices, Suresh Hundia, president of the Bombay Bullion Association, said.                            
	 New Delhi, Aug. 29: Steel companies may hike prices by about Rs 1,000 a tonne within a few days on rise in demand. Steel firms will take a call on this next month after analysing prices of imported steel from countries such as China, SAIL chairman C.S. Verma said.                            
	 New Delhi, Aug. 29: The economic growth data for the first quarter is scheduled to be released on Tuesday. Experts believe that the economy is likely to grow in the range of 8.9 per cent to 9.4 per cent in the quarter despite the partial rollback of stimulus.                            
	 Calcutta, Aug. 29: Tata Steel was awarded the SA 8000 certification for the third time on Friday.                                                                                                                          
